Common.LocationDescription.Common.Text:
Grand Harbor is a master planned development just to the south of the future Spoonbill Reserve development. The 421.05 AC Spoonbill Reserve project is designed to be developed in three separate phases and the approved Conceptual Planned Development (CPD) consists of 460 single-family lots, 412 multi-family units (condos / town homes), and a neighborhood commercial center.

There are 5 separate Grand Harbor neighborhoods that potential purchasers are taking into consideration which are comprised of a total of 142 finished single-family residential lots, 4.45 AC of residential land proposed for 56 multi-family units, and 12.45 AC of commercial land.

​​​​​​​Neighborhoods can be sold together or sold separately. The sale of one neighborhood in a single transaction is acceptable.

From Spoonbill Reserve, north to south, the 5 separate Grand Harbor components are referenced within the table below.​​​​​​​

Common.LocationDescription.Common.Text:
CBRE is pleased to present Spoonbill Reserve, a 421.05 acre development opportunity, situated along the east side of U.S. 1 in Vero Beach, FL. It consists of the northern extension of Grand Harbor, an existing gated master-planned community. 
The Spoonbill Reserve project is designed to be developed in three separate phases and the approved Conceptual Planned Development (CPD) consists of: 

- 460 single-family lots
- 412 multi-family units (condos / townhomes)
- Neighborhood commercial center (maximum of 17,440 sf on an estimated 8.66 acres)

​​​​​​​The development will also include several clubhouse and recreation areas, as well as conservation, preservation, and open space areas all designed around an innovative stormwater treatment facility abutting the existing Spoonbill Marsh property to the east.

Spoonbill Marsh is a 45 acre man-made wetlands area designed and managed by Indian River County to cleanse well-water brine and enhance the natural habitat. The facility offers tour participants an easy, one-mile walk on an existing, elevated boardwalk to view the shallow marshes and associated wildlife. The existing boardwalk system within Spoonbill Marsh will be expanded by 4,100 lf in conjunction with the development of Spoonbill Reserve.

Outside of the adjacent wetlands treatment facility, there are approximately 100 miles of waterfront land in Indian River County, including 21 miles of intracoastal waterway and 23 miles of Atlantic Ocean beaches.

Spoonbill Reserve is located in Vero Beach within central, eastern Indian River County. The County encompasses approximately 497 square miles of land and is approximately 135 miles north of Miami, 190 miles south of Jacksonville, and 98 miles east of Tampa. Indian River County is bordered by Brevard County to the north, St. Lucie County to the south, and both Osceola County and Okeechobee County to the west. The City of Vero Beach is the county seat and other incorporated areas located within the county include Fellsmere, Indian River Shores, Orchid, and Sebastian.

Common.LocationDescription.Common.Text:
CBRE has been retained as the exclusive advisor for the sale of a prime 22 Acre residential development site located at the northwest corner of State Road 60 (20th St.). and Indian Creek Blvd. in unincorporated Indian River County, FL. The property is located 2 miles east of the I-95 20th St. interchange. It’s about the highly regarded Indian Creek Estates senior living community. The subject property is L shaped and has 1,000’ frontage on 20th St. which is a main east-west arterial serving Vero Beach.

The property had previously been approved for a 168 unit condominium project, Vero Groves. The following site plan was recently developed for a 176 unit multi-family residential project with Clubhouse, pool, amenity lake, dog park, and recreational area. The site plan includes 422 parking spaces of which 60 are garaged. Nearby apartment communities are at 100% occupancy with waiting lists. There is clear unmet demand for additional rental units. The property is also suitable for single family attached and detached, townhouse and mixed-use development. 20th St. is the east-west arterial connecting I-95 to downtown Vero Beach. The Indian River Mall is located one mile east on 20th St.

The economy in Vero Beach is stronger than ever and the unemployment rate is at an all-time low. Job growth over the last year has been especially robust. Demographics are also changing. Not only is the region a leading destination for retirees, but the population immigration is spurring additional employment growth to meet increased demand for services.
